title: Putin raised Prigozhin up, used him and it seems he has now destroyed his own creature
description: No one should be sentimental about Yevgeny Prigozhin.

title: Wagner Group commander Dmitry Utkin 'was on plane' that crashed north of Moscow
description: Wagner Group commander Dmitry Utkin was on the plane with Yevgeny Prigozhin that crashed north of Moscow, the Russian civil aviation authority has said.

title: Was Prigozhin on plane that crashed near Moscow? What we know so far
description: A private jet with 10 people on board has crashed in Russia - with the man who led a short-lived mutiny against the country's top brass on the passenger list.

title: Hot dog seller to mercenary boss: Who is Yevgeny Prigozhin?
description: From flea market hot dog seller to the head of a mercenary group behind a mutiny against the Russian military, Yevgeny Prigozhin's rise was far from ordinary.

title: Footage shows Russian jet plummeting to the ground
description: Video has emerged showing the moment a plane - said to have mercenary boss Yevgeny Prigozhin on board - was seen plummeting towards the ground.

title: Greece investigating whether organised arson groups to blame for deadly wildfires
description: Greece is investigating whether organised arson groups are to blame for wildfires which now left at least 20 people dead.

title: Ten killed in private jet crash near Moscow - Wagner leader Yevgeny Prigozhin 'on passenger list'
description: Ten people have been killed in a private jet crash north of Moscow - with the Russian Civil Aviation Authority saying Yevgeny Prigozhin was on the passenger list.

title: Heart-stopping moment followed by jubilation as India's spacecraft lands on moon
description: The tension is palpable in the control centre of the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO). A heart-stopping moment for every scientist and every Indian watching.

title: 'We are under attack': Security fears after report Chinese spy used LinkedIn to target British officials
description: A Chinese spy used LinkedIn to target thousands of British officials and attempt to mine secrets, according to a report.

title: Forget Watergate - here's why the US is facing its most chaotic political period in recent history
description: If you were looking for a point at which to sit up, tune in and get your head around the utterly mad state of American politics, well then the next couple of days is perfect.

title: India joins exclusive club after successful moon landing - with innovative, low-cost spacecraft
description: Nearly four years ago, Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi hugged the director of India's space agency who was reduced to tears after losing Chandrayaan-2 - his country's first attempt to land on the moon.

title: Some tropical rainforest leaves are 'becoming so hot they're reaching critical point'
description: A tiny proportion of leaves in tropical rainforests are getting so hot they are breaching the threshold at which they can photosynthesise, according to a new study.

title: Singing security guard at Taylor Swift concert 'fired'
description: A security guard who went viral after he was filmed singing along at a Taylor Swift concert has claimed he has since been fired by the firm he was working for.

title: Child who was stuck dangling above canyon in cable car says he 'never wants to get on one again'
description: A child has described the "horrific" moment the cable car line snapped in Pakistan, leaving eight people dangling over a 274m (900ft) river canyon for more than 15 hours.

title: Two tankers collide in Suez Canal disrupting traffic
description: Two tankers have collided in the Suez Canal, disrupting traffic in the global waterway for several hours, Egyptian authorities said.

title: India has become first country to successfully land a spacecraft on the moon's south pole
description: India has become the first country to successfully land a spacecraft on the moon's south pole.

title: Heart transplant golfer charged after 'pushing wife against wall', police say
description: A professional US golfer, who survived two heart transplants, has been arrested on domestic abuse charges after allegedly pushing his wife against a wall and throwing her phone into a pool.

title: Video shows police raid at home of 98-year-old woman who died the next day
description: New video shows the moment police officers raided the home of a 98-year-old local newspaper publisher, who died the following day.

title: India-UK trade deal held up by 'sticky' issues as trade secretary visits Delhi
description: Kemi Badenoch heads to India this week in the hope of making progress on a trade deal, but government sources played down the prospect of an imminent breakthrough.

title: Fans pretend random visitor is football club's new player in prank protest at lack of signings
description: Fans of a Spanish football club have greeted a random man arriving at the city's airport as if he was an incoming player, in protest at its lack of activity in the transfer market.

title: Remains of man believed to have died 22 years ago found on glacier
description: The remains of a man who is believed to have died in an accident on a glacier 22 years ago have been found high in the Austrian Alps.

title: Rumours swirl after Xi Jinping unexpectedly pulls out of summit speech
description: Chinese President Xi Jinping unexpectedly pulled out of delivering a speech at the BRICS summit in South Africa - leading to speculation he might be unwell.

title: At least 17 dead in bridge collapse in India
description: At least 17 people have died after a bridge collapsed in India.

title: Polls open in Zimbabwe as opposition seeks to break governing party's 43-year rule
description: The polls in Zimbabwe have opened as the country votes on a president, parliament and local council positions.

title: UK to provide  £192m loan guarantee to boost Ukraine nuclear capabilities
description: Energy secretary Grant Shapps has visited Ukraine to announce fresh financial support for its nuclear fuel supply in a bid to end its reliance on Russia.

title: Moscow threatens to annex breakaway regions of neighbour Georgia
description: Russia's former president Dmitry Medvedev says Moscow could formerly annex two breakaway regions of neighbouring Georgia.
